Hemopericardium: a late complication after repair of pectus excavatum.
 Hemopericardium and tamponade occurred in a 12 year old boy with Marfan's syndrome, two years after surgical repair of pectus excavatum.
 This life-threatening complication resulted from penetration of a fractured metal plate through the pericardium into the right atrium.
 The clinical details are reported and discussed.
